Files:
- platform/browser-extension/src/background-message-handlers.ts (handleBgSetToolPermission, lines 320-361)

Context:
`handleBgSetToolPermission` (line 320) currently handles ALL plugins uniformly by searching `cache.plugins`. Browser tools are NOT in `cache.plugins` — they're in `cache.browserTools`. The `server-state-cache.ts` already has the full browser tool pending update infrastructure:
- `addPendingBrowserToolUpdate(tool, permission)` (line 145)
- `removePendingBrowserToolUpdate(tool)` (line 150)
- `reapplyPendingOptimisticUpdates()` (lines 83-91) already applies `pendingBrowserToolUpdates` to `cache.browserTools`

But `handleBgSetToolPermission` never calls these functions — it uses `addPendingPluginToolUpdate` (line 338) which stores in the wrong map.

Changes:
Add a conditional branch at the top of `handleBgSetToolPermission` (after extracting plugin/tool/permission) for `plugin === 'browser'`:

```typescript
if (plugin === 'browser') {
  const cache = getServerStateCache();
  const originalPermission = cache.browserTools.find(t => t.name === tool)?.permission ?? 'auto';

  const updatedBrowserTools = cache.browserTools.map(t =>
    t.name === tool ? { ...t, permission } : t,
  );
  addPendingBrowserToolUpdate(tool, permission);
  updateServerStateCache({ browserTools: updatedBrowserTools });

  sendServerRequest('config.setToolPermission', { plugin, tool, permission })
    .then((result: unknown) => {
      removePendingBrowserToolUpdate(tool);
      sendResponse(result);
    })
    .catch((err: unknown) => {
      removePendingBrowserToolUpdate(tool);
      const currentCache = getServerStateCache();
      const revertedBrowserTools = currentCache.browserTools.map(t =>
        t.name === tool ? { ...t, permission: originalPermission } : t,
      );
      updateServerStateCache({ browserTools: revertedBrowserTools });
      sendResponse({ error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err) });
    });
  return;
}
```

Then wrap the existing code in an implicit else (it already handles the non-browser case correctly).

Import `addPendingBrowserToolUpdate` and `removePendingBrowserToolUpdate` from `./server-state-cache.js`. Check the existing imports at the top of the file — they already import `addPendingPluginToolUpdate`, so add the browser variants to the same import statement.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change handleBgSetPluginPermission — it already has special handling for 'browser' via `addPendingPluginPermissionUpdate('browser', ...)` and the `reapplyPendingOptimisticUpdates` browser permission overlay (lines 79-82 of server-state-cache.ts).
- Do NOT change server-state-cache.ts — the infrastructure is already complete.
- Do NOT change BrowserToolsCard.tsx — its React-level optimistic update remains as a defense-in-depth layer.

Files:
- platform/browser-extension/src/background-message-handlers.ts (handleBgSetAllToolsPermission, lines 363-413)

Context:
Same structural issue as handleBgSetToolPermission. `cache.plugins.find(p => p.name === 'browser')` returns undefined, making optimistic update, pending registration, and rollback all no-ops.

The `server-state-cache.ts` already exports:
- `addPendingAllBrowserToolsUpdate(toolNames, permission)` (line 155)
- `removePendingAllBrowserToolsUpdate(toolNames)` (line 162)

Changes:
Add a conditional branch at the top of `handleBgSetAllToolsPermission` (after extracting plugin/permission) for `plugin === 'browser'`:

```typescript
if (plugin === 'browser') {
  const cache = getServerStateCache();
  const toolNames = cache.browserTools.map(t => t.name);
  const originalToolStates = new Map<string, ToolPermission>();
  for (const t of cache.browserTools) {
    originalToolStates.set(t.name, t.permission);
  }

  const updatedBrowserTools = cache.browserTools.map(t => ({ ...t, permission }));
  addPendingAllBrowserToolsUpdate(toolNames, permission);
  updateServerStateCache({ browserTools: updatedBrowserTools });

  sendServerRequest('config.setAllToolsPermission', { plugin, permission })
    .then((result: unknown) => {
      removePendingAllBrowserToolsUpdate(toolNames);
      sendResponse(result);
    })
    .catch((err: unknown) => {
      removePendingAllBrowserToolsUpdate(toolNames);
      const currentCache = getServerStateCache();
      const revertedBrowserTools = currentCache.browserTools.map(t => ({
        ...t,
        permission: originalToolStates.get(t.name) ?? t.permission,
      }));
      updateServerStateCache({ browserTools: revertedBrowserTools });
      sendResponse({ error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err) });
    });
  return;
}
```

Import `addPendingAllBrowserToolsUpdate` and `removePendingAllBrowserToolsUpdate` from `./server-state-cache.js`.

Constraints:
- Same constraints as US-001.
- This story is marked as e2eCheckpoint since it completes the browser cache fix — E2E tests from the companion PRD (browser tool permission changes) will exercise both paths end-to-end.
